rComments: Amazingly epic lectures. Sometimes he has some "brain stalls" but other then that he's great. Hot T.A too ;)
Excellent teacher!!

Obviously a theatre prof but I think he forgets that students in classics are also taking this course. As such the historical importance of texts discussed tends to fall to the wayside which is mainly what classics students would be interested in. Gaining approval for essays is also a very tedious process.

Although this professor is clearly passionate about what he teaches, it can be very draining just being spoken to each week with very few chances to actually interact in the lectures (even though students are marked partially on class discussion).  Also, no marks were disclosed to students prior to the drop date for the course.
By far the best theatre prof I have had at the University, interesting, captivating and inspiring. Makes a 3 hour class feel like 10 minutes!

He really adds alot of theatre to his lectures making them really interesting. You can tell he is passionate about what he teaches. Very helpful when asked questions. Points out things in lectures that will be on quizes. However, approval process for essays is time consuming.

I've never before been so inspired. He obviously loves what he does, and as a result you can never be bored in his class. Genuinely kind and really helpful. Lots of work, but very worthwhile. The man is a genius and exceptionally talented.

Inspiring professor! Fantastic human being! Going to his lectures feels like he is in his profession for all the right reasons. He really shows patience during his lectures and when seeking help with the subject matter. Froehlich genuinely wants to help you out - it's a great feeling. The man is an encyclopedia of all things history of theatre!
The man is brilliant, and might I add, very sexy. His genius is captivating and we all love him. He is fantastic and his tangents are fabulous! Thank you Froelich!
great class. tests are hard but essay was pretty easy. make sure you always show up. he takes attendence
He is the most brilliant man I've ever met. I never missed a single class, no matter how sick I was, because he made it so worthwhile to go. An absolute genius, and really, really nice.
This man IS the man when it comes to classic theatre. No room for slacking in his class, though.

He's a great professor, great actor, very interesting and nice guy. And I personally enjoyed it when he got off topic and acted out things from his personal life. Interesting, hilarious and profound guy.
Very intelligent professor. Really knows his stuff . . . a little too many stories and he gets off track a little too much.

Helpful professor but really difficult to take notes during his lectures because he constantly is off topic.  I knew more about the Neptune Theatre in Halifax and a chair he bought than the actual course content.
He is very friendly and interesting. I love his class because he makes it worthwhile to go.
you know in high school when youve got that one teacher that is just so cool, so helpfull, and totally down to earth. he's that and more. amazing prof.
probably the best prof i ever had, he shares his entusiasm with his students.
He is easily the best professor i had in my university career
He's a great guy, but has a problem staying on topic.
Brilliant, lucid,
